            <segmentation>
               <p>The text contains the following units:
                  <list>
                     <item>Segments: A single phonological segment. Encoded by the "seg" element with type=segment</item>
                     <item>Words: A syntactically independent sequence of Segments. Clitics are treated as Words. Encoded using
                     the "w" element.</item>
                     <item>Syllables: Sequence of Segments consisting minimally of a vocalic nucleus. Since Words are syntactically
                     rather than prosodically defined, a Syllable can contain more than one word. Encoded by the "seg" element
                     with type=syllable</item>
                     <item>Lines: Sequence of both Words and Syllables forming a line of verse.</item>
                  </list>
                  The "join" attribute of w and pc elements encodes the manuscript word division.
               </p>
